metadata.name: ULÉ
metadata.description:
Home is where the heart is,  
Where the blue skies stretch wide,  
Where the grass is green and lush,  
And the flowers bloom with pride.

Home is where we feel safe,  
Where we can rest and be free,  
Where we can laugh and love and dream,  
And just be who we wanna be.

Home is where we find peace,  
Where we can escape the noise,  
Where we can sit and watch the clouds,  
And let our worries all dissolve.

Home is where we make memories,  
Where we share our joy and pain,  
Where we grow and learn and change,  
And where we always remain.

So here's to home, sweet ULÉ,  
The place where we belong,  
May it always be a place of love,  
Where our spirits can be strong.




*ULÉ is the word for home, in the Èkìtì dialect of the Yorùbá language.
